The JMUnit 1.0 Final Version was released yesterday, in http://sourceforge.=
net/projects/jmunit/. It's beta version was available for donwloads several=
 weeks ago. There was few modifications in the final version, most of the e=
ffort was in the full documentation of the source-code. The project now is =
targeting in it's divulgation in the developer community of Java ME and the=
 creation of the 1.1 version, with many improvements and some features to J=
ava ME. The JMUnit is totally based in the xUnit, been a library for unit t=
esting similar to JUnit, but for Java Micro Edition. It main advantages are=
 simplicity, been easy to use and a library that really helps the mobile ap=
plication developers. It has two versions, one for each version of the CLDC=
, and it's open-source. It's the first of a some of possible open-source pr=
ojects with the purpose of get better the job of the programmers in that pl=
ataform. In the future, maybe, you'll receive more news about them.
